## Acceptance Criteria

- [x] `Backend` protocol defined with `@runtime_checkable`
- [x] `SparkBackend` implements all protocol methods using `spark.sql()`
- [x] `RestBackend` wraps existing DatabricksClient and implements protocol
- [x] `auto_backend()` correctly detects: in-cluster (DBR env var), external (HOST+TOKEN), offline (None)
- [x] `current_notebook_path()` returns path via SparkConf, dbutils, ipynbname, or stack inspection
- [x] PySpark import is guarded — `ImportError` handled gracefully with helpful message
- [x] `EstimationPipeline` updated to accept a `Backend` instead of raw `DatabricksClient`
- [x] All existing tests still pass
- [x] New unit tests cover auto-detection logic and backend method routing

